Deprecated. - the class has been deprecated, see Content API.

public class FeatureServer
extends BaseWorkspaceLayerSource
implements ServerProxy

a FeatureServer is a type of IMS Service that produces Features in a very compact form suitable for transmission across the internet. The FeatureServer has zero or more Layers, which you can access by obtaining the LayerInfo from the getLayerInfo() method.

getRegistry

public static Registry getRegistry()
Deprecated. 
Returns the LayerExtension registry for FeatureServer and ImageServer. You can register custom LayerExtensions by calling this method, and adding your classes to the registry. You must do this before creating your instance of the FeatureServer class, if you want to be able to interpret your extension AXL from ServiceInfo returned by the server.

Returns:
the registry for LayerExtensions

getLayerSource

public static FeatureServer getLayerSource(String URL,
                                           String serviceName,
                                           String userName,
                                           String password)
                                    throws IOException
Deprecated. 
Creates a FeatureServer client proxy for the given ArcIMS feature service proxy instance. This constructor immediately invokes the refresh() method in order to obtain ServiceInfo from the remote Server.

Parameters:
URL - a url of an ArcIMS site
serviceName - the name of an ArcIMS feature service
userName - a user name to get access to a restricted ArcIMS service
password - a password to get access to a restricted ArcIMS service
Returns:
the feature server instance based on the ArcIMS feature service proxy
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if service is null, limit is < 1, or accuracy <= 1.0
IOException - if any problem occurs when invoking refresh()
See Also:
TileCache
